CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Saved From Possibly Death - Arrow points to heavily thicketed ravine near Leech Farm Veterans Hospital, Penn Township (above), where Mrs. Susie Tinsley was found by police, after being lost for two nights and a day. Thomas Burch (right photo, left to right), his dog and James Patterson, and Gene Edison (second row, same order), John Patterson and David Burch led officers to the area where they last saw her.-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, first row, from left: Thomas Burch, his dog, and James Patterson; second row: Gene Edison, John Patterson, and David Burch, gathered around exterior concrete stairway with metal railing on an overgrown hillside, another version
